.TH SEPGEN 1 "March 2026" "sepgen 0.1.0" "SELinux Policy Tools"
.SH NAME
sepgen \- SELinux policy generator from source code and runtime tracing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sepgen analyze
.I source_path
.RB [ \-\-name
.IR NAME ]
.RB [ \-\-exec\-path
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.br
.B sepgen trace
.I binary
.RB [ \-\-name
.IR NAME ]
.RB [ \-\-pid
.IR PID ]
.RB [ \-y ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.br
.B sepgen refine
.B \-\-name
.I NAME
.RB [ \-\-audit\-log
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-auto ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sepgen
generates SELinux policy modules from source code analysis and runtime
tracing. It produces macro-based .te and .fc files with custom types,
ready to compile with
.BR checkmodule (8)
and install with
.BR semodule (8).
.PP
Three-phase workflow:
.TP
.B analyze
Static analysis of C/C++/Python source code. Detects syscall patterns,
capabilities, socket usage, config paths, and service file directives.
.TP
.B trace
Runtime tracing with
.BR strace (1)
using \-\-secontext for SELinux context awareness. Captures actual file
access, socket operations, and process execution.
.TP
.B refine
Reads AVC denials from
.I /var/log/audit/audit.log
using
.BR avc-parser (1)
and suggests macro additions using
.BR semacro (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "analyze options"
.TP
.BI \-\-name " NAME"
Policy module name (default: derived from source path).
.TP
.BI \-\-exec\-path " PATH"
Override installed binary path for .fc entry.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity (\-v for verbose, \-vv for debug).
.SS "trace options"
.TP
.BI \-\-name " NAME"
Policy module name.
.TP
.BI \-\-pid " PID"
Attach to existing process instead of starting a new one.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-auto\-merge
Auto-approve merge conflicts (trace wins).
.SS "refine options"
.TP
.BI \-\-name " NAME"
Policy module name (required).
.TP
.BI \-\-audit\-log " PATH"
Path to audit log (default: /var/log/audit/audit.log).
.TP
.B \-\-auto
Auto-apply non-aggregate suggestions to .te file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Generate policy from C source
sepgen analyze ./src/ \-\-name myapp

# Trace a binary and merge with existing policy
sepgen trace /usr/sbin/myapp \-y

# Refine policy from AVC denials
sepgen refine \-\-name myapp \-\-auto
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR semacro (1),
.BR avc-parser (1),
.BR strace (1),
.BR semodule (8),
.BR checkmodule (8),
.BR audit2allow (1)
